  "conclusion": "c4 rowchunk layer-limit probe shows final hidden/token outputs are still green at layer limits 4 and 8 for both rowchunk2 and rowchunk3, but rowchunk3 already introduces strict bit drift by layer limit 4 and over-tolerance full-attention trace failures at layer limit 8: decode step 0 / generated index 1 / layer7 attn_input_pre_qkv fails for rows0..2. Rowchunk2 has no such stage failures. The grouped>=3 issue is therefore visible inside the second full-attention layer before it escapes the layer-8 final hidden tolerance, then amplifies to full-model hidden red by decode step 2 and token red by index 82.",
